alias: linearly dependent, linearly independent, linear dependencies, linear dependence, linear independence

Linear dependence

A set of vectors is said to be linearly dependent if at least one vector in the set can be expressed as a linear combination of the other vectors.

We can check for linear dependence/independence between multiple vectors by writing down the following equation:

Hint

Vectors are linearly independent when there are no scalars and other than zero that can make the linear combination equal to the zero vector.

The equation above gives us an homogeneous system of linear equations, and we now gotta check if it has an unique solution or not.

There are two cases:

The coefficient matrix is a square

In this case we just find the determinant.
If then and the system is linearly independent.

Example

The coefficient matrix is rectangular

Use Gaussian Elimination or Gauss-Jordan Elimination on the augmented matrix to find the solution.
If then the vectors are linearly independent.
